<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="pt-BR">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>Views</title>
<style>
body {
  margin:0;
  font-family: Arial;
  background: linear-gradient(135deg,#d1c4e9,#bbdefb);
  animation: fadeIn 1s ease-in;
}

header {
  background:#7e57c2;
  padding:15px;
  display:flex;
  justify-content:center;
  gap:15px;
  box-shadow:0 3px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
}

button {
  background:#e3f2fd;
  border:none;
  padding:10px 20px;
  border-radius:10px;
  cursor:pointer;
  transition: all 0.3s ease;
}

button:hover {
  transform: scale(1.1);
  background:#bbdefb;
}

.container {
  background:white;
  margin:20px auto;
  padding:20px;
  max-width:800px;
  border-radius:15px;
  box-shadow:0 5px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
  animation: slideUp 0.8s ease;
}

footer {
  height:60px;
  background:#5c6bc0;
}

/* animações */
@keyframes fadeIn {
  from {
    opacity:0;
  }
  to {
    opacity:1;
  }
}

@keyframes slideUp {
  from {
    transform: translateY(30px);
    opacity:0;
  }
  to {
    transform: translateY(0);
    opacity:1;
  }
}
</style>
  </head>
<body>

<header>
<button onclick="goTo('/')">Index</button>
<button onclick="goTo('/views')">Views</button>
<button onclick="goTo('/views/package')">Package</button>
</header>

<div class="container">
<h1>O que são Views?</h1>
<p>Views são arquivos responsáveis pela interface visual da aplicação.</p>
</div>

<div class="container">
<h2>Função</h2>
<p>Elas mostram dados ao usuário de forma organizada.</p>
</div>

<footer></footer>

<script>
function goTo(r){window.location.href=r}
</script>

</body>
</html>